{"lemma":"مُذَكَّرٌ","slug":"مُذَكَّرٌ","root":"ذ.ك.ر","root_slug":"ذ-ك-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ذ-ك-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مُذَكَّرٌ","root":"ذكر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13945"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%B0%D9%8E%D9%83%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%B1%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"masculine","tags":["masculine"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"masculine","tags":["masculine"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"reminder","examples":[{"text":"فَذَكِّرْ إِنَّمَآ أَنتَ مُذَكِّرٌ","english":"So remind, (O Muḥammad); you are only a reminder."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the passive participle of the verb ذَكَّرَ (ḏakkara, “to make masculine”).\n\nDerived from the active participle of the verb ذَكَّرَ (ḏakkara, “to remind”)."},"ipa":["/mu.ðak.kar/","/mu.ðak.kir/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13945","headword_ar":"مُذَكَّرٌ","root":"*kr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"masculine"},{"kind":"text","text":"word; a word"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made mas-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":971},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"culine"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu*ak~arapN","text_ar":"مُذَكَّرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"A she-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling a hecamel in make and in disposition."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And also, (K, TA,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu*okarapN","text_ar":"مُذْكَرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (accord. to the CK,) A woman"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who makes herself like a male;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*akarapN","text_ar":"ذَكَرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, and so in a copy of the K,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*akirapN","text_ar":"ذَكِرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in another copy of the K, and in the TA,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*akorapN","text_ar":"ذَكْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the CK,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muta*ak~irapN","text_ar":"مُتَذَكِّرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu*ak~arapu Alv~unoyaA","text_ar":"مُذَكَّرَةُ الثُّنْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"A she-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a large head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like that of a he-camel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) because her head is one of the parts that are excepted in the game of chance [called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almayosir","text_ar":"المَيْسِر"},{"kind":"text","text":"] for the man who has sold her: [therefore those parts are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~unoyaA","text_ar":"الثُّنْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":":] (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling the make of the male in"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the largeness of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the head and legs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, M in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vnY","text_ar":"ثنى"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomN mu*ak~arN","text_ar":"يَوْمٌ مُذَكَّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A day that is severe, distressing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hard to be borne;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu*okirN","text_ar":"مُذْكِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which a severe fight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slaughter, has taken place."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*akarN","text_ar":"ذَكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence but one.] ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAhiyapN mu*ak~arapN","text_ar":"دَاهِيَةٌ مُذَكَّرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A severe calamity"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"misfortune;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu*okirN","text_ar":"مُذْكِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"because it is from this epithet applied to a she-camel as meaning \"bringing forth a male;\" for her doing so was disliked, as has been mentioned voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*akarN","text_ar":"ذَكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) or the latter means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which none can withstand but strong, courageous, stubborn men."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*akarN","text_ar":"ذَكَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places, in the latter half of the paragraph."}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}